headline.main: VISIT TO BRITAIN REVISES OPINIONS; Isolationist Congressmen Are Convinced of Sincerity of British War Effort

lead_paragraph: LONDON, Nov. 29 -- Five members of the House of Representatives who have been here for ten days said tonight that they would start their journey home tomorrow sadder but wiser men for their ex- perience. They remain divided as to how far the United States should carry its aid, but have reached agreement on the extent and sincerity of Britain's own war effort.
abstract: Repr Maas says Brit has done a bad job in U S
